<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - FRONT COVER, VIBRATION DAMPER, and GEROTOR OIL PUMP - Cleaning,
        Inspection, and Testing - Gerotor Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Gerotor Oil Pump</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wash all parts thoroughly in a suitable solvent.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes. Limit
                    compressed air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dry parts with filtered compressed air. See .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay front cover assembly on workbench.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect gerotors and housing for nicks, burrs or scoring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace any damaged components.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The inner and outer gerotors are a matched set and cannot be replaced individually.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If installing new gerotors, correct orientation is not necessary. If installing old gerotors,
                        correct orientation is necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place inner and outer gerotors into oil pump housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350512" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1358.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 231. Gerotor inspection</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front cover assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer gerotor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge to inspect wear by checking the radial clearance between outer gerotor
                and oil pump housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350513" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1359.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 232. End clearance check for oil pump</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer gerotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inner gerotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler gauge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check oil pump end clearance as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With the gerotors in place in the front cover, place Straightedge across housing.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert feeler gauge under Straightedge at inner and outer gerotors. Compare end
                    clearance with specifications .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If measurements are not within specifications, install new gerotors (as a set).</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350513.1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/d1367.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 233. Oil pressure regulator components</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">End cap and O-ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pressure bypass spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston poppet</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a 12 mm hex head wrench to remove the oil pressure regulator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect oil pressure regulator components and bore for wear.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
